🚀 Deploy Server (CD Machine Setup)
(Deployer David Machine – Ritik Hub)
________________________________________
🎯 Purpose of the Deploy Server
On the Build Server, we already:
•	Built the application 
•	Created the Docker image 
•	Pushed the image to ECR 
👉 Now, the Deploy Server is responsible for:
•	Pulling the Docker image from ECR 
•	Running the container 
•	Making the application accessible to users 
________________________________________
❓ Why Do We Need ECR Here?
🔴 Problem:
•	The Docker image exists only on the Build Server 
•	The Deploy Server cannot access it directly 
________________________________________
✅ Solution: Amazon ECR
Amazon ECR acts as a central storage (registry) for Docker images.
________________________________________
🎯 Why ECR is Needed:
•	📦 Centralized image storage 
•	🔁 Easy sharing between servers 
•	🔐 Secure access via AWS IAM 
•	🚀 Enables scalable deployments 
________________________________________
🧠 Deployment Flow
ECR
⬇
Deploy Server
⬇
Pull Image
⬇
Run Container
⬇
Application Live
________________________________________
🏗️ Step 1: Create EC2 Instance (Deploy Server)
________________________________________
👉 Go to AWS Console:
•	EC2 → Launch Instance 
________________________________________
Fill Details:
•	Name: Deployment-Server 
•	AMI: Amazon Linux 2023 
•	Instance Type: t2.micro / t3.micro 
•	Key Pair: Create or use existing 
________________________________________
🌐 Network Settings:
Click Edit → Add rule:
•	Type: Custom TCP 
•	Port: 8080 
•	Source: 0.0.0.0/0 
👉 Also ensure:
•	SSH (22) is allowed 
________________________________________
▶️ Launch Instance
________________________________________
🔐 Step 2: Connect to Deploy Server
ssh -i build-key.pem ec2-user@<PUBLIC-IP>
________________________________________
🔧 Step 3: Install & Configure Docker
________________________________________
Install Docker
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install docker -y
________________________________________
Start Docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
________________________________________
Give Permission to ec2-user
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user
________________________________________
⚠️ Important Note:
After running the above command:
exit
ssh -i build-key.pem ec2-user@<PUBLIC-IP>
👉 You must reconnect for Docker permissions to apply
________________________________________
🔐 Step 4: Configure AWS & Login to ECR
________________________________________
Configure AWS (if not already done)
aws configure
Enter:
•	Access Key 
•	Secret Key 
•	Region (must match ECR, e.g., ap-south-1 or us-east-1) 
________________________________________
Login to ECR (Correct Command)
aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin 637423650512.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
________________________________________
✅ Expected Output:
Login Succeeded
________________________________________
📥 Step 5: Pull Docker Image from ECR
________________________________________
Command:
docker pull <ECR-URI>:latest
________________________________________
Example:
docker pull 637423650512.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/quest3-demo-app:latest
________________________________________
🎯 Output:
•	Docker image downloaded to the Deploy Server 
________________________________________
🔍 Step 6: Verify Image
docker images
________________________________________
You should see:
•	Repository: quest3-demo-app 
•	Tag: latest 
________________________________________
▶️ Step 7: Run Container
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 <ECR-URI>:latest
________________________________________
Example:
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 637423650512.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/quest3-demo-app:latest
________________________________________
🌐 Step 8: Access Application
________________________________________
Open in browser:
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:8080
________________________________________
🎯 Final Result
•	Docker image pulled from ECR 
•	Container running successfully 
•	Application accessible via browser 
________________________________________
🧠 Final Understanding
Component	Role
Build Server	Build & push Docker image
ECR	Store Docker image centrally
Deploy Server	Pull & run the application
________________________________________
